 terraform destroy and terraform apply -destroy

Both do the same thing — destroy all resources.

terraform destroy

asks confirmation → destroys all resources
no plan file support

terraform apply -destroy

shows plan first → asks confirmation → destroys all resources
supports -out flag to save plan

# save destroy plan
terraform plan -destroy -out=destroy.plan

# review plan
terraform show destroy.plan

# execute
terraform apply destroy.plan

Summary:

terraform destroy              → quick destroy ✅
terraform apply -destroy       → destroy with plan file support ✅✅

terraform apply -destroy is preferred in production — you can review and save the destroy plan before executing.

